1
00:00:44,503 --> 00:00:46,505
[gentle music playing]

2
00:01:01,896 --> 00:01:03,397
[exhales deeply]

3
00:01:03,939 --> 00:01:05,733
Oh. Good morning, Daniel-san.

4
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:07,401
Morning.

5
00:01:07,485 --> 00:01:09,904
Welcome to Miyagi family dojo. You like?

6
00:01:10,863 --> 00:01:13,073
This is really something.
Who are all these guys?

7
00:01:13,157 --> 00:01:14,784
[Mr. Miyagi] All of Miyagi ancestor.

8
00:01:15,951 --> 00:01:16,994
And who's that?

9
00:01:17,578 --> 00:01:20,498
Ah, that is Miyagi Shimpo Sensei.

10
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:24,668
First Miyagi bring karate to Okinawa.

11
00:01:24,752 --> 00:01:28,589
Like all Miyagi,
Shimpo Sensei was fisherman.

12
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:30,090
Love fishing.

13
00:01:30,174 --> 00:01:31,383
Love sake.

14
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:37,264
One day, strong wind,
strong sun, strong sake,

15
00:01:37,932 --> 00:01:39,099
but no fish.

16
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:43,479
Shimpo Sensei fall asleep
off coast of Okinawa,

17
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:46,273
wake up off coast of China. [chuckles]

18
00:01:46,357 --> 00:01:47,942
[uplifting music playing]

19
00:01:48,025 --> 00:01:49,819
[Mr. Miyagi] The Han family took him in,

20
00:01:50,778 --> 00:01:52,863
taught him art of kung fu.

21
00:01:55,658 --> 00:01:57,910
When Sensei return to Okinawa,

22
00:01:58,536 --> 00:02:00,329
Miyagi karate was born.

23
00:02:01,038 --> 00:02:03,916
Two culture, two martial art.

24
00:02:04,834 --> 00:02:07,419
Two branches, one tree.

25
00:02:07,503 --> 00:02:12,299
A bond that kept Hans and Miyagis
connected still today.

26
00:02:40,786 --> 00:02:41,954
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

27
00:02:56,343 --> 00:02:57,344
[gasps]

28
00:02:57,845 --> 00:02:59,805
[suspenseful music playing]

29
00:02:59,889 --> 00:03:01,849
[in Mandarin] Master Han! Master Han!

30
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:05,477
The Doctor is coming.

31
00:03:07,146 --> 00:03:09,607
Stall her. Go.

32
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:11,817
Get Li!

33
00:03:11,901 --> 00:03:14,278
The Doctor! Li, the Doctor!

34
00:03:16,655 --> 00:03:18,324
The Doctor!

35
00:03:18,991 --> 00:03:20,993
Welcome to Han Academy.

36
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:23,787
Are you looking to learn Kung Fu?

37
00:03:23,871 --> 00:03:26,248
Never too late to start
even for an old woman.

38
00:03:26,332 --> 00:03:28,542
We start with jacket on - jacket off.

39
00:03:28,626 --> 00:03:32,254
Take off jacket, put on jacket.

40
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:35,633
I know he told you to stall me.

41
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,886
I did nothing of the sort.

42
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,056
He did ask. Sorry.

43
00:03:42,681 --> 00:03:43,682
Go!

44
00:03:43,766 --> 00:03:44,767
[chuckles]

45
00:03:46,977 --> 00:03:48,395
Where is my son?

46
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:50,814
Tea?

47
00:03:54,276 --> 00:03:55,986
[Dr. Fong] I'm not here for tea.

48
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:57,571
Where is Li?

49
00:03:58,864 --> 00:04:00,366
Kung Fu is very empowering...

50
00:04:00,449 --> 00:04:02,034
Uncle,

51
00:04:02,117 --> 00:04:04,411
with all due respect.

52
00:04:04,495 --> 00:04:08,290
I already lost one son to your "path."

53
00:04:09,208 --> 00:04:13,170
I will not lose another.

54
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:14,254
I understand.

55
00:04:15,297 --> 00:04:17,466
[Dr. Fong] I know what Li means to you...

56
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:20,594
but I will not have him put in harm's way.

57
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:22,429
[Mr. Han] We both agree.

58
00:04:22,513 --> 00:04:25,683
If you could only see
how Kung Fu helps him -

59
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:28,560
Each time life knocked me down,

60
00:04:28,644 --> 00:04:31,146
Kung Fu helped me find my way back
to the proper path.

61
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:38,362
This is for you.

62
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:39,571
What's this?

63
00:04:39,655 --> 00:04:41,407
I got a new position -

64
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:43,575
- at a hospital in New York.

65
00:04:44,118 --> 00:04:45,327
New York?

66
00:04:45,411 --> 00:04:48,580
It's a chance to restart for both of us.

67
00:04:51,375 --> 00:04:52,459
Why two hats?

68
00:04:52,543 --> 00:04:55,546
So you can give one to Li...

69
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:58,298
...when he finds the courage
to come out from behind your screen.

70
00:04:58,382 --> 00:05:00,467
[in English]
Xiao Li, I'll see you tonight at dinner.

71
00:05:04,138 --> 00:05:05,139
[in Mandarin] Very smart.

72
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:09,643
Your mother.

73
00:05:09,727 --> 00:05:10,728
[Li huffs]

74
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:11,812
W--

75
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:15,774
[pensive music playing]

76
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:18,193
Were you even going to ask me?

77
00:05:19,445 --> 00:05:20,446
[in English] Oh, there you are.

78
00:05:21,155 --> 00:05:22,281
I'm sorry.

79
00:05:22,364 --> 00:05:24,408
Xiao Li, would you like to
move to New York?

80
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:26,243
No, Mom, our life's here.

81
00:05:26,869 --> 00:05:28,829
And how long were you gonna keep this
a secret from me?

82
00:05:28,912 --> 00:05:31,331
And which one of us is keeping secrets?

83
00:05:32,499 --> 00:05:34,251
I was training. Not fighting.

84
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:37,129
You practice violence,
you get violence in return.

85
00:05:37,212 --> 00:05:38,672
You of all people should know that.

86
00:05:39,673 --> 00:05:43,010
Xiao Li, there will be so many
other things for you in New York.

87
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:46,096
Why are you speaking in English, Mom?

88
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:47,556
New city, new language.

89
00:05:48,265 --> 00:05:50,350
And you can leave all this stuff here.

90
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:55,689
Hey! Can I have your gloves?

91
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:57,983
Whatever.

92
00:05:58,484 --> 00:05:59,610
["Home" playing]

93
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:04,364
♪ Darling, won't you take me home? ♪

94
00:06:05,616 --> 00:06:10,954
♪ Send me shivers somewhere I used to go ♪

95
00:06:12,039 --> 00:06:15,125
♪ Wrap my name across your mouth ♪

96
00:06:15,209 --> 00:06:18,170
♪ When I let my feelings down ♪

97
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:21,799
♪ Darling, won't you take me home? ♪

98
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:23,675
[horns honking]

99
00:06:24,885 --> 00:06:27,262
♪ Yeah, won't you take me ♪

100
00:06:27,346 --> 00:06:30,224
♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh-oh ♪

101
00:06:30,307 --> 00:06:31,433
[bicycle bell rings]

102
00:06:31,517 --> 00:06:34,686
♪ Tell me, does your mother know? ♪

103
00:06:36,605 --> 00:06:39,942
♪ Like the back of my car on a sunny day ♪

104
00:06:40,025 --> 00:06:42,778
♪ You're the song on the radio
I never play ♪

105
00:06:42,861 --> 00:06:45,864
♪ You're the words in my soul
That I wanna say ♪

106
00:06:45,948 --> 00:06:47,574
♪ That I wanna say ♪

107
00:06:47,658 --> 00:06:48,659
♪ Won't you make me say? ♪

108
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:52,746
♪ Won't you take me home? ♪

109
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:58,627
♪ Send me shivers somewhere I used to go ♪

110
00:06:58,710 --> 00:06:59,711
[song fades]

111
00:07:03,006 --> 00:07:05,050
[sighs] The boxes arrived.

112
00:07:07,803 --> 00:07:10,139
Oh. It's nice.

113
00:07:11,723 --> 00:07:12,724
[sighs]

114
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:16,145
[Dr. Fong sighs]

115
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:20,440
Go check out your room.

116
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:28,323
[horns honking,
sirens blaring in distance]

117
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:35,747
-[Li] Hey, Mama.
-Hmm?

118
00:07:35,831 --> 00:07:37,875
I'm gonna try to find
something for dinner, all right?

119
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:39,459
I think I saw a pizza place
around the corner.

120
00:07:39,543 --> 00:07:41,628
-Well, don't go too far.
-Sure.

121
00:07:41,712 --> 00:07:43,005
And be careful.

122
00:07:43,088 --> 00:07:44,339
I'm always careful.

123
00:07:44,423 --> 00:07:46,425
["Tick-Tick" playing]

124
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:50,596
♪ Never knew life would be a big dipper ♪

125
00:07:50,679 --> 00:07:52,306
♪ Always gotta be a little bit slicker ♪

126
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:55,017
♪ Got room to improve with the groove
Gonna make the beat quicker ♪

127
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,101
♪ Tick-tick-ticker ♪

128
00:07:56,185 --> 00:07:58,478
♪ Why have people gotta be meaner?
Make things cleaner ♪

129
00:07:58,562 --> 00:08:00,981
♪ Work on demeanor
Reach for the sky, be a dreamer ♪

130
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:02,441
♪ Life'll be a little bit sweeter ♪

131
00:08:02,524 --> 00:08:04,651
♪ When the day comes
When you finally meet her ♪

132
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:22,920
[entry bell rings]

133
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,550
Can I help you?

134
00:08:28,634 --> 00:08:29,635
Uh, yeah.

135
00:08:29,718 --> 00:08:32,846
Do you guys have, um,
like, a stuffed crust?

136
00:08:32,930 --> 00:08:35,098
[scoffs, chuckles]

137
00:08:35,182 --> 00:08:37,184
[chef] No, we don't have stuffed crust.

138
00:08:37,768 --> 00:08:39,436
But you know what?
I think I can help you out.

139
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:41,271
You need to get back in your car,

140
00:08:41,355 --> 00:08:43,315
drive through the Holland Tunnel
to Jersey,

141
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:44,900
go 20 miles in any direction,

142
00:08:44,983 --> 00:08:47,194
find yourself a nice,
crappy little strip mall,

143
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:49,238
and I'm sure you can find a stuffed crust.

144
00:08:49,321 --> 00:08:50,572
Are you guys done?

145
00:08:50,656 --> 00:08:52,115
[chuckles]

146
00:08:52,616 --> 00:08:55,410
Hi. I apologize on behalf of these morons.

147
00:08:55,494 --> 00:08:56,495
Oh!

148
00:08:56,578 --> 00:08:57,913
-One of whom is my dad.
-I'm a moron?

149
00:08:57,996 --> 00:09:00,082
Um, we don't have stuffed crust.

150
00:09:00,165 --> 00:09:02,918
We have plain, pepperoni,
sausage and peppers,

151
00:09:03,001 --> 00:09:04,962
Grandma's, Sicilian, eggplant.

152
00:09:05,045 --> 00:09:07,798
Uh. Yeah. Pepperoni. Let's do pepperoni.

153
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:09,299
Pepperoni it is. Anything else?

154
00:09:09,383 --> 00:09:10,342
Toilet paper?

155
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:13,262
[diner laughing] What? Toilet paper.

156
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:15,639
Sorry.

157
00:09:15,722 --> 00:09:17,224
Context: I just moved in down the street,

158
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,184
so I'm trying to pick up
some stuff for the apartment.

159
00:09:19,268 --> 00:09:20,727
Is there a place nearby that's open?

160
00:09:20,811 --> 00:09:23,897
Preferably one where I don't
have to drive an hour to Jersey,

161
00:09:23,981 --> 00:09:25,482
'cause I just flew in 18 hours
from Beijing.

162
00:09:26,358 --> 00:09:27,359
[chuckles]

163
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,945
Yeah, yeah.
There's a bodega around the corner.

164
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:31,822
-Uh...
-Convenience store.

165
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:33,282
We call them bodegas here.

166
00:09:33,365 --> 00:09:37,202
Oh. Weird. Cool.
Thanks. I'll be right back.

167
00:09:37,286 --> 00:09:38,495
Uh, can I get a name for the order?

168
00:09:39,621 --> 00:09:40,872
Yeah. Li Fong.

169
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:43,208
Welcome to New York, Li Fong.

170
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:45,127
Thanks.

171
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:46,712
-[entry bell rings]
-What?

172
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:48,630
Since when did you get so charming?

173
00:09:49,631 --> 00:09:51,425
Someone in this place needs to be.

174
00:09:52,175 --> 00:09:53,176
[diner] Ouch.

175
00:09:55,053 --> 00:09:58,557
Ah. School starts at 7:45 sharp.
You take the L train to--

176
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:02,102
To Union Square and then I transfer
to the Six to Canal. Yeah.

177
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:03,729
-And then you see Ms. Morgan.
-Ms. Morgan.

178
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:06,148
She's gonna give me the schedule.
I got it, Mom.

179
00:10:06,982 --> 00:10:08,066
I think.

180
00:10:08,734 --> 00:10:11,987
Um, how about you?
First day at the hospital. Ready?

181
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:13,405
I got it.

182
00:10:14,698 --> 00:10:15,824
I think.

183
00:10:18,493 --> 00:10:19,911
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

184
00:10:19,995 --> 00:10:22,205
["Please" playing]

185
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:26,626
♪ I seen a lot of keys in my life, uh ♪

186
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,796
♪ Got people wanna please in my life, uh ♪

187
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:32,341
♪ Got varying degrees in my life, uh ♪

188
00:10:32,883 --> 00:10:35,260
♪ If only I could seize
All the right stuff ♪

189
00:10:35,344 --> 00:10:38,096
♪ Get rid of the disease in my life, uh ♪

190
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:40,849
♪ Oh, the birds and bees in my life, uh ♪

191
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:43,435
♪ What's the forest from the trees
In my life, uh ♪

